What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Pediatric Growth Hormone Deficiency Market?

Market Analysis and Size

The rise in the prevalence of pituitary gland tumors and rising healthcare expenditure are the major factors influencing the market growth rate. Furthermore, advancements in medical technology, growing government funding, and rising initiatives by public and private organizations to spread awareness about eye diseases are the factors that will expand the pediatric growth hormone deficiency market. Other factors such as a rise in the number of endocrine disorders and an upsurge in the number of cases associated with short stature will positively impact the market growth rate. Also, a growing number of pediatric diagnostic campaigns and programs in underdeveloped nations will result in the expansion of the pediatric growth hormone deficiency market.

Data Bridge Market Research analyzes that the global pediatric growth hormone deficiency market which was USD 3.45 billion in 2023, is likely to reach USD 13.87 billion by 2031, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 19.00% during the forecast period. “Blood tests” dominate the diagnosis segment of the market due to the growing demand for blood tests for growth hormone diagnosis. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include depth expert analysis, patient epidemiology, pipeline analysis, pricing analysis, and regulatory framework.

